The authors present in this volume three contributions analysing the main features of **prophecy in Israel and Assyria**: *chapter 1* focuses on the prophet Amos, contextualising his action within his historical framework; *chapter 2* describes the historical background behind the prophetism of Zephaniah; *chapter 3* defines the basic traits of prophetical composition in the Neo-Assyrian period. 

[These three contributions help in understanding similarities and differences between prophecies in Israel and Assyria, contextualising each prophetic experience in its historical milieu.]

